# Implementation Plan - Janus’ Crypto Sisig Cinematic Scroll

This plan outlines the creation of a high-energy, cinematic landing page for "Janus’ Crypto Sisig" using a 300-frame scroll animation.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - The 300 frames in `c:/New folder (2)` are quite large in total size. I will implement a robust preloading strategy to ensure a smooth initial experience.
> - Mobile users will have a reduced frame count (120 frames) for performance.

## Proposed Changes

### Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Vite + React
- **Animation**: GSAP + ScrollTrigger
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS with CSS Variables (GSAP theme)
- **Icons**: Lucide React

### Components

#### [NEW] [ScrollEngine.jsx](file:///C:/New%20folder%20(2)/src/components/ScrollEngine.jsx)
- Handles the canvas rendering of the 300 frames.
- Tie scroll progress to `currentFrame` index.
- Implements lazy loading for frames beyond the first 50.

#### [NEW] [OverlayUI.jsx](file:///C:/New%20folder%20(2)/src/components/OverlayUI.jsx)
- Contains the textual and UI elements (Logo, CTA, Pricing).
- Uses ScrollTrigger to animate opacity, position, and scale of elements based on specific frame ranges (e.g., 1-60, 61-110, etc.).

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///C:/New%20folder%20(2)/src/index.css)
- Implement 8px grid system.
- Define global colors (Neon Green, Fire Red, Dark Emerald).
- Add support for `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None planned for this visual-heavy project.

### Manual Verification
- Scroll through the entire 300-frame sequence to verify transitions.
- Check responsiveness on different screen widths.
- Verify that "New folder (2)" frames load correctly.
- Test performance (FPS) during scroll.
